 <!-- Introduction -->
 <!-- The introduction should start as shown: -->
 <purpose>
   <p>
     This part of ISO 10303 specifies an application module for the
     representation of resources required to achieve a specified objective.
   </p>
   <example>Examples of required resources are:
      <ul>
      <li>Spare parts 
      </li>
      <li>Material
      </li>
      <li>Persons with known skills
      </li>
      <li>Facilities
      </li>
      <li>Technical documentation
      </li>
      <li>Transportation services
      </li>
      <li>etc
      </li>
      </ul>
   </example>
   <note number="1">A resource requirement that is identifiable is represented as <express_ref 
       linkend="required_resource:arm:required_resource_arm.Required_resource_item"/>.
   </note>
   <note number="2">A resource requirement that has to be specified is represented as <express_ref 
       linkend="required_resource:arm:required_resource_arm.Required_resource_specification"/>.
   </note>
   <example number="1">A spare part with part number "KSB 1234" is a identifiable resource - <express_ref 
       linkend="required_resource:arm:required_resource_arm.Required_resource_item"/>.
   </example>
   <example number="2">The replaceble unit with part number "KSB 1234" and serial number "123-456" is a identifiable resource - <express_ref 
       linkend="required_resource:arm:required_resource_arm.Required_resource_item"/>.
   </example>
   <example number="3">A person with social sequrity number "501022-2345" is a identifiable resource - <express_ref 
       linkend="required_resource:arm:required_resource_arm.Required_resource_item"/>.
   </example>
   <example number="4">The need for 240 V power supply is a requirement specification - <express_ref 
       linkend="required_resource:arm:required_resource_arm.Required_resource_specification"/>.
   </example>
   <p>Resource requirements may have the following characteristics:
      <ul>
      <li>A resource requirement can be specified or identified 
      </li>
      <li>Resource requirements can be grouped
      </li>
      <li>A resource requirement can be quantified
      </li>
      <li>A resource requirement or resource requirement grouping can be classified.
      </li>
      </ul>
   </p>
   <p>The following are not enabled by this module alone but are enabled by modules that use this module:
      <ul>
      <li>Identification assignment
      </li>
      <li>Property, date and descriptive representation assignment
      </li>
      <li>Recording of the organizations or people in organizations who identify an item as satisfying a resource need
      </li>
      <li>Scheduling
      </li>
      <li>Location
      </li>
      <li>Effectivity 
      </li>
      <li>Approval
      </li>
      <li>Conditions.
      </li>
      </ul>
   </p>
   <note number="1">A required resource can be given an identifier using the 
         <module_ref linkend="identification_assignment:1_scope">
     	   Identification assignment
         </module_ref> module.
   </note>
   <note number="2">A required resource and/or a required resource relationship can be given a dated effectivity using the 
         <module_ref linkend="Effectivity:1_scope">
     	   Effectivity
         </module_ref> module.
   </note>
 </purpose>

